    <fr:title text="Young's Inequality">Young's Inequality</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
    <fr:date>
      <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
      <fr:month>5</fr:month>
      <fr:day>26</fr:day>
    </fr:date>
    <fr:authors>
      <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
    </fr:authors>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> be a positive integer, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p < +\infty ]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q]]></fr:tex> be its <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001W.xml" addr="FA-001W" title="Conjugate exponents">conjugate</fr:link>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a, b \geq  0]]></fr:tex> be two positive numbers. Then,</fr:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ab \leq  \frac {a^p}{p} + \frac {b^{q}}{q}]]></fr:tex>
  </fr:mainmatter>
