            <fr:title text="Conjugate exponents">Conjugate exponents</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>In the context of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p]]></fr:tex> spaces and related inequalities, two exponents <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p, q \in  [1, \infty ]]]></fr:tex> are said to be conjugate (or Hölder conjugates) if they satisfy:</fr:p>
            <fr:p>
              <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\frac {1}{p} + \frac {1}{q} = 1]]></fr:tex>
            </fr:p>
            <fr:p>Given a value of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>, its conjugate <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q]]></fr:tex> can be calculated as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q = \frac {p}{p-1}]]></fr:tex>. Some common pairs of conjugate exponents are:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p = 1]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q = \infty ]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p = 2]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q = 2]]></fr:tex> (self-conjugate)</fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p = 4/3]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q = 4]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p = 3/2]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q = 3]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ul>
            <fr:p>Conjugate exponents play a crucial role in many important inequalities in functional analysis and the theory of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p]]></fr:tex> spaces, including:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:link type="local" href="FA-001Y.xml" addr="FA-001Y" title="Hölder inequality">Hölder's inequality</fr:link>: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||fg||_{1} \leq  ||f||_{p} ||g||_{q}]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>The fact that the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001Q.xml" addr="FA-001Q" title="Dual space">dual space</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p]]></fr:tex> is isomorphic to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^q]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1 \leq  p < \infty ]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:link type="local" href="FA-001X.xml" addr="FA-001X" title="Young's Inequality">Young's inequality</fr:link> for products: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ab \leq  \frac {a^p}{p} + \frac {b^q}{q}]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a, b \geq  0]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
